    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 111890.0,
      "end_time": 115250.0,
      "text": "of the connection between the financial statements."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 115250.0,
      "end_time": 118040.0,
      "text": "The statement of cash flows is divided into three activities--"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 118040.0,
      "end_time": 120410.0,
      "text": "operating, investing, and financing."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 120410.0,
      "end_time": 122270.0,
      "text": "Descriptions of each of these activities"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 122270.0,
      "end_time": 124460.0,
      "text": "has already been covered in a previous video,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 124460.0,
      "end_time": 126830.0,
      "text": "but let&#39;s just review them quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 126830.0,
      "end_time": 129500.0,
      "text": "Financing is activities that fund the company,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 129500.0,
      "end_time": 131900.0,
      "text": "either through debt or equity."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 131900.0,
      "end_time": 134420.0,
      "text": "Investing is activities that result from buying and selling"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 134420.0,
      "end_time": 138190.0,
      "text": "property, plant, and equipment, intangibles, or investments."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 138190.0,
      "end_time": 139940.0,
      "text": "Operating is the activities that a company"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 139940.0,
      "end_time": 144170.0,
      "text": "does every day, selling or delivering goods or services."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 144170.0,
      "end_time": 145850.0,
      "text": "To obtain an in-depth understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 145850.0,
      "end_time": 147680.0,
      "text": "of these activities, please see my video"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 147680.0,
      "end_time": 149484.0,
      "text": "on business activities."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 149484.0,
      "end_time": 150900.0,
      "text": "The statement of cash flows can be"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 150900.0,
      "end_time": 154310.0,
      "text": "prepared using the direct or indirect method."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 154310.0,
      "end_time": 157430.0,
      "text": "There is no difference between the direct and indirect method"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 157430.0,
      "end_time": 160070.0,
      "text": "for both the investing and financing activities section"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 160070.0,
      "end_time": 161450.0,
      "text": "of the cash flow."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 161450.0,
      "end_time": 163700.0,
      "text": "Under both methods, these two activities"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 163700.0,
      "end_time": 165380.0,
      "text": "are exactly the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 165380.0,
      "end_time": 168710.0,
      "text": "That is not true, however, for operating activities."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 168710.0,
      "end_time": 171290.0,
      "text": "The direct method lists the inflows and outflows"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 171290.0,
      "end_time": 175130.0,
      "text": "for each type of operating activity a company performs."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 175130.0,
      "end_time": 177200.0,
      "text": "Cash flow categories shown include"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 177200.0,
      "end_time": 180320.0,
      "text": "cash collected from customers, cash paid to suppliers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 180320.0,
      "end_time": 183440.0,
      "text": "and cash paid to employees, just to list a few."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 183440.0,
      "end_time": 186200.0,
      "text": "This method is considered more informative for stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 186200.0,
      "end_time": 188330.0,
      "text": "and their decision making, because it clearly"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 188330.0,
      "end_time": 192000.0,
      "text": "shows the sources and uses of cash from operations."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 192000.0,
      "end_time": 194370.0,
      "text": "The indirect method focuses on the differences"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 194370.0,
      "end_time": 197220.0,
      "text": "between net income under accrue accounting and cash"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 197220.0,
      "end_time": 200340.0,
      "text": "from operating activities under cash accounting."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 200340.0,
      "end_time": 203820.0,
      "text": "It starts with net income and adjusts for non-cash items,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 203820.0,
      "end_time": 206310.0,
      "text": "such as adding back depreciation expense"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 206310.0,
      "end_time": 209580.0,
      "text": "or deducting a decrease in accounts payable."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 209580.0,
      "end_time": 211920.0,
      "text": "The indirect method is more difficult for users"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 211920.0,
      "end_time": 212940.0,
      "text": "to understand."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 212940.0,
      "end_time": 215670.0,
      "text": "But that does not stop approximately 98%"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 215670.0,
      "end_time": 218490.0,
      "text": "of all US, European, and Canadian companies"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 218490.0,
      "end_time": 221250.0,
      "text": "from using the indirect method to calculate cash flows"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 221250.0,
      "end_time": 223140.0,
      "text": "from operating activities."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 223140.0,
      "end_time": 224190.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 224190.0,
      "end_time": 227880.0,
      "text": "Because it is easier and less costly to prepare."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 227880.0,
      "end_time": 229830.0,
      "text": "Are there any benefits for stakeholders"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 229830.0,
      "end_time": 233010.0,
      "text": "who use the statement of cash flows to assess a business?"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 233010.0,
      "end_time": 234150.0,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 234150.0,
      "end_time": 237330.0,
      "text": "One benefit for stakeholders is that the indirect method may"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 237330.0,
      "end_time": 239250.0,
      "text": "highlight earnings management."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 239250.0,
      "end_time": 240180.0,
      "text": "How?"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 240180.0,
      "end_time": 243090.0,
      "text": "By highlighting the difference between net income and cash"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 243090.0,
      "end_time": 244740.0,
      "text": "flows from operations."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 244740.0,
      "end_time": 246420.0,
      "text": "We will further explore this concept"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 246420.0,
      "end_time": 248169.0,
      "text": "when we cover the development of cash flow"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 248169.0,
      "end_time": 250370.0,
      "text": "statements in a later video."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 250370.0,
      "end_time": 252470.0,
      "text": "Considering the popularity of the indirect method"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 252470.0,
      "end_time": 254660.0,
      "text": "for the development of the statement of cash flows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 254660.0,
      "end_time": 256160.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll be using the statement of cash"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 256160.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259160.00000000003,
      "text": "flows indirect method for purposes of these videos."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 259160.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261200.00000000003,
      "text": "I will, however, also quickly show"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 261200.0,
      "end_time": 263960.0,
      "text": "you the direct method for comparison purposes."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 263960.0,
      "end_time": 266960.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s do a quick check of your understanding so far."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 266960.0,
      "end_time": 270615.0,
      "text": "The payment of interest on a long-term loan is considered--"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 276320.0,
      "end_time": 280550.0,
      "text": "the answer is definitely not D. All cash outflows are included"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 280550.0,
